wiki.content: ​"Dark Thoughts" is a single by American rapper Lil Tecca, released on March 14, 2025, through Republic Records and Galactic Records. It serves as the lead single from his forthcoming fifth studio album, Dopamine. ​ Background and Composition The track was co-written by Lil Tecca (Tyler-Justin Sharpe), Danish producer Lucas Scharff, and French producer Folie's, with production handled by Scharff and Folie's. Musically, "Dark Thoughts" features an upbeat and bouncy melody reminiscent of Pharrell Williams's work with The Neptunes, drawing particular comparisons to songs like "Frontin'" and "Beautiful". The song is set in D♭ minor, has a tempo of 102 BPM, and follows a 4/4 time signature. ​ Critical Reception Critics have highlighted "Dark Thoughts" as a showcase of Lil Tecca's artistic growth. Michael Saponara of Billboard described it as an example of Tecca "getting in his pop bag," delivering a "soundtrack to a night out on the rooftop bars" and elevating "his artistry to new heights". Devin Morton of HotNewHipHop noted that the song demonstrates Tecca's evolution into a more capable songmaker, calling "Dark Thoughts" a contender for "the best track of his career" and praising its infectious chorus. ​ Wikipedia Commercial Performance "Dark Thoughts" achieved moderate international chart success. In Australia, it peaked at number 22 on the ARIA Top 50 Singles Chart and reached number 4 on the ARIA Hip Hop/R&B Singles Chart. The song also charted in several other countries, including New Zealand (number 11), Iceland (number 16), Latvia (number 11), and Denmark (number 34). ​ Wikipedia Release Formats The single was released digitally, with versions including a clean intro, explicit intro, and an instrumental track. ​ Beatsource Notable Cover Versions As of April 2025, there are no widely recognized cover versions of "Dark Thoughts".​ Music Video An official audio video for "Dark Thoughts" was released on Lil Tecca's YouTube channel on March 14, 2025.
